Year = {2026},
Volume = {96},
Month = {MAY},
Abstract = {Face recognition based on kinship identification is limited by
   ethnicity, image conditions and environmental factors, which are too
   critical when it comes to facial recognition applications in social
   media, forensics and genealogical applications. Face recognition based
   on kinship identification is limited by ethnicity, image conditions and
   environmental factors, which are too critical when it comes to facial
   recognition applications in social media, forensics and genealogical
   applications. The improvements over traditional models are related to
   accuracy and equity; in order to improve on these shortcomings, we
   introduced a new deep learning architecture using an improved version of
   the YOLOv5 backbone, within the context of a multi-task learning
   framework. The model uses two attention mechanisms,
   Squeeze-and-Excitation (SE), and Convolutional Block Attention Module
   (CBAM), to maximize the representation of spatial and channel-wise
   features and Content-Aware Reassembly of Features (CARAFE) to keep the
   high-temperature kinship traits. This system reaches an accuracy of 90
   \% in identifying kinship and shows a validated improvement in equitable
   performance with an Equal Opportunity Difference (EOD) of 0.027 across
   demographic groups. This holds the potential of Artificial Intelligence
   in Bioinformatics and Network Science to act as a fair decision-making
   system and be social impactful.},
