   Saeed Ashraf and Basha, Beriham and Badshah, Amir and Al-Buriahi, M. S.},
Title = {Machine learning-driven design of near-infrared absorbing dyes for
   high-performance photovoltaics},
Journal = {JOURNAL OF PHYSICS AND CHEMISTRY OF SOLIDS},
Year = {2026},
Volume = {210},
Month = {MAR},
Abstract = {The machine learning (ML) based predictors were employed to predict the
   absorption maxima (Amax) of approximately 700 existing dyes. Different
   types of ML models were used and highest R2 (0.89) and lowest RMSE (39
   nm) values were calculated with Random Forest being the better model
   among the used models. A new library of dyes was constructed using a
   tool developed in Python and the absorption maxima of these new
   candidates were estimated using the Random Forest model. Out of 10000
   generated dyes, only 30 dyes (1161-1213 nm) showing absorption in the
   extended spectrum were chosen. This was in order to determine the
   Synthetic Accessibility (SA) of the selected dyes, further to have a
   more defined list of probable dyes which can be synthesized easily. The
   ML framework generates actionable theoretical information that directs
   experimental chemists toward developing the next-generation dyes in
   synthesis.},
