Abstract = {In this work, a regression framework based on multi-model stacking was
   constructed using the CoRE-MOF database, validated for transferability,
   and applied for large-scale prediction on the h-MOF library. The model
   exhibited strong generalization (R2 = 0.943) and effectively identified
   high-performance candidates, with the top 30 predicted MOFs showing
   superior adsorption capacities in GCMC simulations compared with
   synthesized CoRE-MOF structures. This screening strategy provides an
   efficient tool for discovering high-performance MOFs and a data-driven
   perspective for adsorption material design.},
