   Metal-Organic Frameworks for CO2 Capture},
Journal = {CHEMISTRYSELECT},
Year = {2025},
Volume = {10},
Number = {37},
Month = {SEP 25},
Abstract = {Metal-organic frameworks (MOFs) has been extensively employed in CO2
   capture because of high Brunauer-Emmett-Teller (BET) surface area, large
   pore volume, modifiability, and designability. The high diversity of
   metal clusters and organic ligands offers both hope and challenges for
   the design of novel MOFs with excellent CO2 adsorption performance. Here
   we propose an automated nanoporous materials discovery method, powered
   by machine learning and genetic algorithm, for the generative design of
   MOFs. We demonstrate the automated design process of MOFs, with the goal
   of efficiently capturing CO2. The method provides a theoretical study
   for the design of MOFs with the ability to selectively capture CO2.},
